Hochtief Raises 2011 Guidance After Leighton Sells Businesses

-- B y   R a j i v   S e k h r i
-- 
2011-09-30T09:05:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/hochtief-raises-2011-guidance-after-leighton-sells-businesses.html
Hochtief AG (HOT)  raised its prior
guidance for 2011 after its Australian subsidiary  Leighton
Holdings Ltd. (LEI)  sold parts of its Australian iron ore
business at a substantial profit.  Leighton sold several projects undertaken by its subsidiary
HWE Mining in the Pilbara region to mining group  BHP Billiton 
for 512 million euros, generating a profit after tax of 118.5
million euros.  Hochtief said it will specity its guidance in more detail
in coming weeks.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rajiv Sekhri at 
 rsekhri1@bloomberg.net  